East Valley Estate Planning Council
Arizona State Bar — Trusts and Estates Section

<strong>Based in</strong>
Mesa, Arizona — where he was born, raised, and still lives.

  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>A Note on Jay Allen</h2>
    <p>McKay practices alongside Jay Allen, Esq., one of the most experienced estate planning attorneys in the East Valley, who brings more than 25 years of Arizona estate planning practice to the firm as Of Counsel. Clients benefit from McKay's preparation and Jay's depth — a combination that gives this boutique firm a level of collective experience that most solo practices can't offer.</p>

  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-section">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Where is McKay Tucker licensed to practice?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>McKay is licensed to practice law in Arizona. Mesa Estate Planning serves clients throughout Arizona, with a primary focus on Mesa, Chandler, Gilbert, Tempe, Queen Creek, and the broader East Valley.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How long has McKay been practicing estate planning law?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>McKay graduated from Arizona State University Sandra Day O'Connor College of Law in 2023 and has focused on estate planning and business law since entering practice. Prior to founding Mesa Estate Planning, he worked at McCullough Law, where his practice included complex trust and estate planning work for high-net-worth individuals, founders, and executives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What makes Mesa Estate Planning different from other firms?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>McKay built this firm around a single idea — that the quality of estate planning available to wealthy founders and executives should be accessible to every Arizona family. The process, the attention, the level of explanation and follow-through — none of it is reserved for clients with large estates. Every client gets the same standard of care.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Does McKay work with clients outside of Mesa?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. While the firm is based in Mesa, McKay works with clients throughout Arizona. Many consultations and follow-up meetings can be conducted remotely for clients who prefer it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    function toggleFaq(btn) {
      const item = btn.closest('.faq-item');
      const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item.open').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('open'));
      if (!isOpen) item.classList.add('open');
    }
  </script>
</ServiceLayout>
